{
  "doc_id": "586",
  "text": "Since passes between teammates can be modeled as interactions within a network, a variety of previous methods have taken a network approach to studying passing sequences. [CITATION_1] focus on exploratory network analysis to explain key facets of the game like key players and specific team play styles, where the roles of different players on a team level are explained through weighted graphs of passing frequencies. [CITATION_2] calculate rebound probability with spatial coordinates to measure team and player performance via graph theory. [CITATION_3] implement a continuous-time stochastic block model to cluster players based on passing networks.",
